  "title": "Videographer & Short‑Form Video Creator",
  "description": "<p>We’re looking for a hands-on videographer to lead end-to-end short‑form video production: ideation, trend-led creative planning, filming, editing and technical camera operation. You’ll work with strategists and account teams to produce regular, platform-native assets that meet creative and performance objectives.</p><p>Key responsibilities:</p><ul><li>Generate weekly content ideas and content calendars tailored to client briefs and platform best practices.</li><li>Scout and adapt TikTok trends into on‑brand concepts quickly.</li><li>Create pre-production materials: shot lists, storyboards, scripts and schedules.</li><li>Operate camera, lighting and audio equipment on location and in-studio; direct talent and small crews.</li><li>Edit vertical-first videos: cutting, pacing, sound design, captions/subtitles, color grading and basic motion graphics.</li><li>Iterate edits using performance feedback and creative testing results.</li><li>Maintain and manage equipment; recommend upgrades and workflows.</li><li>Present concepts to clients and incorporate feedback to final deliverables.</li></ul><p>Requirements</p><ul><li>2+ years professional videography/short-form content experience (agency or in‑house preferred).</li><li>Portfolio of platform-native short-form videos (TikTok/Reels/Shorts) showing ideation → execution. Provide links.</li><li>Proficient with DSLRs/mirrorless, gimbals, audio recorders and lighting setups.</li><li>Strong editing skills in Premiere Pro, Final Cut Pro or equivalent; After Effects or motion graphics a plus.</li><li>Deep familiarity with TikTok mechanics (sounds, hooks, pacing, captions) and other vertical-first formats.</li><li>Fast turnaround, organized, able to manage multiple projects.</li></ul><p>What we offer</p><ul><li>Exposure to diverse brand briefs and performance data.</li><li>Travel opportunities with Content Creators.</li><li>Collaborative and fast-moving team environment.</li><li>Flexible working arrangements where applicable, equipment support and training budget.</li><li>Competitive compensation (details discussed during interview).</li></ul>",
